O lovely springs that breaking forth,
  From all the hills declare,
A symphony of natureâ€™s worth,
  In harmony and prayer.

The rivers roll, and clouds drift by,
  The mountains meet the sky,
And in their silent majesty,
  O let my spirit fly!

